Responsibilities
About Us Allianz IT is an innovative IT unit which is developing and maintaining state of the art IT solutions for internal and external users. As a multinational organization our IT department is offering the opportunity to work with international teams, projects and partners.Allianz IT is using best practice methodologies like ITIL and CMMI Level 3, TMMI Level 3. Joining Allianz IT you will see that working for an insurance company in IT is not equal to boring legacy technology and applications! We have it all: Top notch infrastructureServer farms, virtualization, SAN, security appliances, high availability appliances and setups.Top notch middleware frameworks and applicationsESB, MQ, DI, DQ, BPM, BRMS, DMS, BAM – need more acronyms?Interesting application developmentMobile and tablet applications, SPA Web applications, portals, software integration and automation Job DescriptionDevelop, support and evolve best in class mobile apps that will deliver rich experience to customers.Works with internal technical teams to identify and build platform elements required to support key mobile product features.Collaborate closely with architects, user interface designers, middleware engineers, and multiple groups to define and implement product features.Build high-level user interfaces using rapid prototyping methodologies.Creates Technical Requirements Documentation based on Product Requirement Documents.Implements upgrades, rebuilds and additional porting of applications.Evaluate opportunities to bring new product features and content to mobile users from a technical perspective.Juggles multiple tasks and projects simultaneously in a results-oriented environment. Required Experience, Knowledge and Skills 2+ years industry experience writing mobile applications for IOS 6/7 and/or Android SDK Level 14+4+ Working experience with an objective oriented language (Java, C++, Objective-C, C#, or similar).Experience writing unit tests using Android/iOS testing frameworks.Knowledge of web services, specifically REST APIs over JSON.Experience using RESTful APIs to integrate mobile applications to server side systems.Knowledge of Maps, Location based Services and Mobile Sensors is required.Knowledge of multithreading.Solid debugging skills.Strong knowledge of Java and the Android SDK and/or strong knowledge of Objective C and the iPhone SDKWorking knowledge of Eclipse and SCM: SVN, Git...Excellent analytical and problem solving skills.Experience with agile software development.Expert in UI design and rapid prototyping.Ability to implement SQL queries.Ability to analyze requirements.Working knowledge of HTML5, CSS3, and Javascript a big plus.Apache Cordova and/or Phonegap is a big plus.The ability to maintain high coding standards and a clear understanding of performance best practices are a big plus.Maven is a plus.Experience with C/C++, Kernel modifications, embedded systems a plus.Results-driven, able and willing to go the extra mile to get the job done.
